VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bDELETE\s+FROM\s+[^\s]+\s+WHERE\s+.*=.*\$.*
WHEN EXPR MISSING:PreparedStatement|setString\(|setInt\(|setLong\(|setObject\()
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects DELETE statements with direct use of user input, increasing the risk of SQL injection.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: Non-parameterized DELETE Statements.
